The paper deals with learning algorithms for multi-view datasets, which is a common problem in machine learning and data mining. The paper proposes a new approach that utilizes both visible and hidden views, which suggests that it could be relevant to several sub-categories. Specifically, cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) are the most likely categories, as they are the most general and encompass a wide range of topics related to learning algorithms. The paper's focus on web data mining and multimedia information analysis also suggests that it could be relevant to cs.IR (Information Retrieval), cs.MM (Multimedia), and cs.CV (Computer Vision).
